  "texts": [
    "However, we relied on FIAPF as the only available concrete list that reflects the hierarchical positions of festivals and is used by the film industry as a quality and reliability standard for producers, distributors, and sales agents.",
    "We also enriched film data with the gender of the director and producer based on the first names of the crew listed on the Cinando database.",
    "We used a large (N = 694, 410) gendered names database [70] derived from Wikipedia to match names with binary gender.",
    "The latter is a limitation of the database; we acknowledge that gender exists on a multidimensional continuum.",
